\newlabel{fig:fig4}{{5}{12}{Equal-bits comparison showing MSE ratio (Rateless / Standard) ranging from 1.01x to 1.93x. The theoretical prediction ($1 + d^2/k^2$) matches experimental results. Rateless MinHash trades statistical efficiency for progressive estimation capability}{figure.5}{}}
